Information on how to qualify and the application process are also provided.

content: You may qualify for Social Security or Supplemental Security Income (SSI) disability benefits if you are considered “legally blind.” You are considered legally blind if your vision cannot be corrected to better than 20/200 in your better eye, or if your visual field is 20 degrees or less.

title: VA Community Living Centers (Formerly Nursing Homes)
content: Provides skilled care to Veterans with significant functional impairments.

title: VA Online Rx Refill for Veterans
content: Learn how to get a refill on a prescription written by a VA doctor.

title: VA Blind Rehabilitation Services (BRS)
content: Provides rehabilitation programs for low vision and blind Veterans, and pursues innovative service delivery models. Links to blind rehabilitation centers.

title: VA Special & Limited Benefits
content: Learn about health care benefits that are offered only to certain Veterans or to Veterans under special situations.

title: VA Special Health Registry Examination Programs
content: Provides information on health registries for eligible Veterans to determine if health problems may be related to environmental exposures during military service. Registries include Gulf War, depleted uranium, Agent Orange and ionizing radiation.

title: VA Spinal Cord Injury & Disorders (SCI&D) Services
content: Support, promote, and maintain the health, independence, quality of life, and productivity of individuals with SCI&D throughout their lives. Download a fact sheet about VA spinal cord injury centers, medical care and other benefits available from the VA.

title: VA Toll-Free Contact Numbers
content: Access VA telephone numbers for education, benefits, income verification and means testing, life insurance, mammography, special issues, headstones/markers and telecommunications devices for the deaf (TDD).

title: VA's Ask a Question - IRIS
content: Submit a question to the VA's Inquiry Routing and Information System (IRIS), which provides answers to questions within five business days on a full range of VA-related subjects.

title: Vaccines
content: Learn about required and recommended vaccines and their safety from the Military Vaccine Agency (MILVAX).

title: Veterans Health Administration (VHA)
content: Learn about eligibility for benefits, copays and charges, family member benefits, special programs and vocational rehabilitation. Click here to access an application for care.

title: Veterans & Families: Transition of Care
content: Provides information for Veterans and their families when transitioning from the DoD to the VA health care system. Includes information on VA policies, services and benefits, as well as fact sheets on specific health concerns related to military service.

title: Spina Bifida Health Care Program
content: Covers most healthcare services and supplies that are medically or psychologically necessary for the treatment of conditions related to spina bifida. The VA can also reimburse expenses for travel to and from the doctor or health care facility.Some services require specific advance approval or preauthorization.

title: Payments for Children with Spina Bifida whose Parents Served in Vietnam or Korea
content: Learn about how people with spina bifida who are natural children of Vietnam and Korea Veterans may be eligible for a monthly monetary allowance.

title: VA - Health Care - Dental Care
content: Receive outpatient dental treatment as an eligible veteran, which may include the full spectrum of diagnostic, surgical, restorative, and preventive procedures. In many cases, however, the law permits only limited kinds of care.

title: VA - Health Care - Foreign Medical Program
content: Receive VA coverage as a service-connected Veteran living abroad for certain necessary health care services associated with the treatment of those service-connected conditions.

title: Gulf War, Agent Orange and Ionizing Radiation Registry Program
content: Learn about the registry and exams available for Veterans who may have been exposed to ionizing radiation, agent orange, and/or depleted uranium.

title: VA - Health Care - Health Insurance for Dependents (CHAMPVA)
content: Find information about CHAMPVA, a comprehensive health care program in which the VA shares the cost of covered health care services and supplies with eligible beneficiaries.

title: VA - Health Care - Home Based Primary Care
content: Provides comprehensive, interdisciplinary, primary care in the homes of veterans with complex medical, social, and behavioral conditions for whom routine clinic-based care is not effective.

title: VA - Health Care - Nursing Home Care
content: Find out about eligibility requirements for nursing home care through the VA.Priority is given to veterans with service-connected disabilities. If space and resources are available, other veterans may be considered.

title: VA - Health Care - Pharmacy Service
content: Learn about eligibility requirements and how to apply for VA pharmacy services.VA Pharmacy Service provides prescription drugs and medical supplies from VA pharmacies to eligible veterans. The prescriptions may be received at a VA pharmacy or mailed to your home address.

title: Readjustment Counseling (Vet Centers)
content: Find information about Vet Centers including - locations, eligibility, counseling services, support groups, employment counseling, assistance with applying for benefits and much more all in a confidential setting.

title: Services and Aids for Blind Veterans
content: Learn about personal and social adjustment programs and medical or health-related services for eligible blinded veterans at selected VA Medical Centers maintaining blind rehabilitation centers.

title: Veterans Alcohol and Drug Dependence Rehabilitation Program
content: Provides medical, social, vocational, and rehabilitation therapies to eligible alcohol and drug dependent veterans. The programs offer various forms of treatment including detoxification, rehabilitation, and psychiatric care. Treatment programs are located in VA medical centers and clinics.

title: Veterans Prosthetic Appliances
content:
Provides medically prescribed prosthetic and sensory aids to eligible veterans. These aids include artificial limbs, hearing aids, communication aids, eyeglasses, orthopedic braces and shoes, wheelchairs, crutches and canes.
For additional information, contact the prosthetic representative at the nearest VA medical center or outpatient clinic.

title: VA Travel Reimbursement
content: Learn the eligibility requirements for VA travel reimbursement and contact information for the program.

title: VA Office of Tribal Governmental Relations
content: Outlines the VA's responsibilities to Tribal Governments and the Veterans of the Tribes. Explains the methods of collaboration and consultation the VA has and will implement in serving the Tribes.

title: Center for Minority Veterans
content: Offers minority Veterans a resource center for accessing information about VA benefits, services and programs.

title: VA Life Insurance Policies
content: Provides information on the life insurance policies offered by the VA to Service Members, Veterans, disabled Veterans and their family members.

title: VA Benefits in Brief
content: Provides an overview of the benefits available from the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) and contact information so you can apply. Includes information about disability and survivors’ benefits, different types of life insurance, as well as education and employment programs for Veterans and their families.

title: Fact Sheet - Applying for Caregiver Support
content: Find information on how to apply for caregiver benefits from the Department of Veterans Affairs.

title: VA National Center for Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
content: Advances the clinical care and well-being of America's Veterans through research, education and training in the science, diagnosis and treatment of PTSD and stress-related disorders.

title: VA Care Management & Social Work Services
content: Works to maximize health and well being, through the use of psychosocial interventions for Veterans, families and caregivers in VA health settings.

title: Navy Safe Harbor Case Management
content: Assigns a care professional to help sailors and Coast Guardsmen identify short- and long-term goals and develop plans to achieve them. Also anticipates and addresses the day-to-day non-medical needs of enrolled Service Members and their families and works to resolve any problems that arise during recovery.

title: Guide to VA Mental Health Services for Veterans & Families
content: Details mental health services are available to Veterans at local and regional VA health care facilities.

title: VHA Directive 2010-054 - Catastrophically Disabled Veterans
content: Covers the clinical evaluation and eligibility for Veterans who are catastrophically disabled.

title: VA Patient Aligned Care Team (PACT)
content: Implements a patient-centered medical home (PCMH) model at all  Veterans Health Administration (VHA) Primary Care sites. Provides accessible, coordinated, comprehensive, patient-centered care and is managed by primary care providers with the active involvement of other clinical and non-clinical staff.

title: Claim Form for Combat-Related Special Compensation (CRSC)
content: Access the DoD form to fill out to apply for Combat-Related Special Compensation.

title: DOL Form 384 - Certification of Qualifying Exigency for Military Family Medical Leave
content: Use Form 384 to apply for Military Family Medical Leave. Fact Sheet 28 explains how FMLA works for active duty and the call to active duty. DOL's Frequently Asked Questions provides answers to how FMLA operates.

title: DOL Form 385 - Certification for Serious Injury or Illness for Military Family Leave
content: Use Form 385 to medically certify illness or injury that exists in connection with requesting Military Family Medical Leave.

title: DD Form 149 - Application for Correction of Military Record
content: Use DD Form 149 to request correction of military records.

title: Department of Navy Electronic Forms
content: Download forms needed during Marine Corps service by type and number.

title: Navy Personnel Command (NAVPERSCOM) Forms
content: Open and fill out forms from this online library.

title: Navy Recruiting Command Forms
content: Find a list of forms for the Navy Recruiting Command that can be downloaded and filled out.

title: DD2648 Preseparation Counseling Checklist for Active Component Service Members
content: Find an online version of this form that can be filled out electronically or printed.

title: DD2944 Claim for Retroactive Stop-Loss Pay
content: Download and print this form to submit for retroactive stop-loss special pay for all branches.

title: Database of VA Forms
content: Provides a comprehensive database of VA forms and instructions for completing all applications.

title: Traumatic Servicemembers' & Veterans' Group Life Insurance (TSGLI) Claim Form & Branch of Service Contact Information
content: Provides general information about the TSGLI claim form and TSGLI branch of service contact information.

title: VA Form 10-10EZ - Application for Medical Benefits
content: Use this easy to use on-line form to apply for Veterans benefits or update your information.

title: VA Form 21-526 - Application for Compensation &/or Pension
content: Use Form 21-526 to apply for compensation and/or pension. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: VA Form 0220 - Notice of Right to Appeal
content: Provides instruction and deadlines for filing an appeal following denial of a motion for benefits. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: VA Form 21-22A - Appointment of Individual as Claimant's Representative
content: Use Form 21-22a to appoint a Veterans Service Organization as your claims representative. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: VA Form 21-4138 - Statement in Support of Claim
content: Use Form 21-4138 to provide VA with a statement that supports claims for benefits. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: VA Form 4597 - Rights to Appeal Decision by the Board of Veterans Appeal
content: Provides information and instructions on filing an appeal against the Board of Veterans Appeal's final decision about your claim. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: VA Forms 4107 - Right to Appeal VA Decision
content: Provides information and instructions on filing an appeal against the VA decision about your claim. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: VA Form 10-5345 - Request for Copy of Health Information
content: Use Form 10-5345 to request a copy of personal health information.  The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and information regarding this application.

title: VA Form 28-1900 - Disabled Veterans Application for Vocational Rehabilitation
content: Use Form 28-1900 to apply for vocational rehabilitation. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: VA Form 28-8832 - Application for Counseling
content: Use Form 28-8832 to apply for counseling with the VA. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: VA Form 21-527 - Income Net Worth & Employment Statement
content: Use VA Form 21-527 to apply for disability pension if you have previously filed a claim for compensation and/or pension. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: VA Form 21-8940 - Application for Increasing Compensation Based on Unemployability
content: Use Form 21-8940 to claim compensation benefits based on unemployability due to a service-connected disability. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: Application for Annual Clothing Allowance
content: Learn about eligibility for an annual clothing allowance for Veterans with disabilities whose medications and prosthetics cause damage to their clothing.

title: Catalog of Federal Government Forms
content: Provides a database of federal government forms including Veteran benefit and social security forms.

title: VA Form 26-1880 Request for a Certificate of Eligibility
content: Fill out, print and submit this form to request proof of military service that qualifies for VA benefits and Veteran status.

title: VA Form 10-10CG
content: Provides information and instructions on applying for the VA's Comprehensive Assistance Family Caregivers Program. The VA Forms Database may have additional information on filling out this application.

title: VA Form 180 - Request Pertaining to Military Records
content: Use Form 180 to request military records. Additional information is also available about obtaining DD-214 and other military records.

title: VA Form 21-4142 - Authorization to Release Information to VA
content: Use Form 21-2142 to authorize the release of medical and other information to the VA. The VA Forms Database may have additional forms and instructions for this application.

title: Army Non-Service-Connected Death Compensation
content: Provides general overview of non-service-connected death benefits for Active Duty members, retirees and Veterans.

title: Hubbard Act
content: Read the law that provides sole survivors a number of benefits already offered to those honorably separating from military service.

title: Military Compensation - Survivor Benefits Plan
content: Provides information on the military Survivor Benefits plan, which pays eligible survivors of military retirees an inflation-adjusted monthly income.

title: Month of Death Benefits Payment Information
content: Learn how surviving spouses can apply for VA compensation or pension benefit for the month of the Veteran's death.

title: MyArmyBenefits
content: Learn about Army benefits, including pay, education, family services, health care, life insurance, soldier services, transitioning and retirement, Social Security, casualty/survivor and VA benefits.

title: MyArmyBenefits - Casualty & Survivor Assistance
content: Provides both general and individualized benefits information to the survivors of a fallen soldier.

title: Navy Mutual Aid Association
content: Provides life insurance and annuity products, assists Service Members and survivors in securing federal benefits and provides education on financial security matters.

title: Reserve Component Survivor Benefit Plan
content: Provides information on Survivor Benefit Plan compensation for members of the Reserve Component. Links to a Reserve survivor benefits calculator and fact sheet on the right sidebar of the page.

title: Social Security Benefits for Widows, Widowers & Other Survivors
content: Learn about Social Security benefits available to widows, widowers and other family members.

title: Survivor Benefits
content: Answers many questions about DoD Survivor Benefit programs.

title: Survivors' & Dependents' Educational Assistance (DEA) Program
content: Provides education and training opportunities to eligible dependents of certain Veterans. A fact sheet on the VA SDEA program is also available.

title: VA Benefits for Survivors
content: Provides information on survivor benefits including Dependency & Indemnity Compensation (DIC), the Survivors' and Dependents' Educational Assistance Program (DEA) and other programs. Learn more about the DEA program.

title: VA Retroactive Payment for Deceased Veterans
content: Learn about the VA's actions to identify and pay surviving spouses who are eligible to receive a one-time compensation or pension payment for the month of the Veteran's death.   Surviving spouses should contact the Survivors Call Center at 1-800-749-8387.

title: VA Survivor Benefits Information
content: Provides quality information and assistance to family members suffering a loss and what benefits are available to them through the VA.

title: Veterans' Widows/ers International Network, Inc.
content: Provides support to Veterans and retiree widows across the country by assisting with benefits and claims, keeping aware of new legislative changes and news affecting benefits, and providing a sense of togetherness with other Veterans' widows/ers.

title: Parents' Dependency & Indemnity Compensation (DIC)
content: Provides a basic monthly payment for an eligible surviving spouse. The monthly payment is increased for each dependent child, and also if the surviving spouse is housebound or in need of aid and attendance. VA also adds a transitional benefit to the surviving spouse's monthly DIC if there are children under age 18. The amount is based on a family unit, not individual children. Surviving parents are also eligible for this program.

title: Survivors' and Dependents' Educational Assistance Program (DEA)
content: Provides education and training opportunities to eligible dependents and survivors of certain Veterans.

title: VA - Survivor's Payments - Death Pension
content: Death pension is a benefit paid to eligible dependents (surviving spouse and/or child) of deceased wartime veterans whose deaths were not related to military service. Learn more about the application process and contact numbers.

title: VA - Survivors' Payments - Dependency and Indemnity Compensation (DIC)
content: The Veterans Dependency and Indemnity Compensation (DIC) is a monthly check paid to eligible survivors. To be eligible for this program, you must be the child, spouse, or parent of a veteran who died while serving in active military duty or as a result of a service-connected disability.

title: VA Office of Survivors Assistance
content: Serves as a resource regarding all benefits and services provided by the VA to survivors and dependents of deceased Veterans and members of the Armed Forces.

title: Benefits.gov - Burial Benefits Overview
content: Learn about who qualifies for VA burial benefits and how to apply for them. This link provides basic information with additional links for other burial benefits.

title: VA Burial Benefits
content: Provides information on VA burial benefits.

title: Headstones and Markers for Placement in Private Cemeteries
content: Receive a government headstone or marker free of cost for members of the Armed Forces of the United States who die while on active duty or any veteran who was discharged under conditions other than dishonorable.Certain National Guard and reserve members may also qualify.

title: Burial Benefits - Partial Reimbursement of Expenses
content: Find information on VA burial allowances for service-connected and non-service connected deaths.

title: Burial Benefits - Presidential Memorial Certificates
content: Honor the memory of honorably discharged deceased veterans with a Presidential Memorial Certificate (PMC),an engraved paper certificate, signed by the current President.

title: Army Survivor Benefits Calculator
content: Calculate estimated survivor benefits as a current, former or future spouse of a member of the Army.

title: VA Benefits in Brief
content: Provides an overview of the benefits available from the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) and contact information so you can apply. Includes information about disability and survivors’ benefits, different types of life insurance, as well as education and employment programs for Veterans and their families.

title: Paid-up Survivor Benefit Plan Program
content: Explains how the Paid-up Survivor Benefit Plan Program (SBP) operates for military retirees and the rebuttal period. The SBP also applies to participants in the Retired Serviceman's Family Protection Plan (RSFPP).

title: Warrior Care
content: Provides links to resources for warrior care, including service programs, DoD and VA resources, news and events, and more.

title: Fort Campbell Survivor Outreach Services (SOS)
content: Find resources for survivors by contacting Fort Campbell SOS, which provides services to the Garrison and communities closest to where families live in a holistic and multi-agency approach.

title: Armed Forces Crossroads - Casualty & Loss
content: Find information and links that provide a wealth of information on loss, while acting as a support network for those in need.

title: Burial At Sea
content: Answers questions about performing a 'burial at sea' for military personnel.

title: A Survivor's Guide to Benefits
content: A handbook from the Department of Defense for the families of deceased Service Members.

title: The Veterans Consortium Pro Bono Program
content: Provides free attorneys to Veterans and family members who have an appeal pending at the U.S. Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims.

title: Marine Corps Wounded Warrior Regiment (WWR) District Injured Support Coordinators
content: Conduct face-to-face visits and telephone outreach to wounded, ill and injured Marines and their families to support psychological health, legal, benefits, employment, housing and other areas.

title: U.S. Army Warrior Care & Transition Program (WCTP)
content: Enables the Army to evaluate and treat soldiers through a comprehensive, soldier-centric process of medical care, rehabilitation, professional development and achievement of personal goals.

title: Navy Mutual Aid Association

title: VA Form 21-22
content: Request a representative from a Veterans Service Organization (VSO) to represent you when you apply for VA benefits.

title: National Veterans Legal Services Program (NVLSP)

content: Provides professional representation to American Veterans and their dependents seeking benefits through the federal benefits system.

title: National Native American Veterans' Association
content: Dedicated to helping Native American Veterans receive benefits from their military service regardless of tribal affiliation, degree of Native American blood or branch of service.

title: Veterans' Widows/ers International Network
content: Reaches out to Veterans' widows/ers across the United States and overseas to provide fellowship and assist them with identifying and claiming survivor benefits. Also keeps survivors abreast of new legislation and news affecting benefits.

title: Warrior Care

title: U.S. Army Warrior Transition Command (WTC)

title: Navy Safe Harbor
content: Provides non-medical support to seriously wounded, ill, and injured Sailors and Coast Guardsmen, as well as their families. Assists service members throughout their recovery, rehabilitation, and reintegration. For more assistance call 1-877-746-8563 or email safeharbor@navy.mil.
